<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>CS 自学笔记 on CS Note</title><link>https://lzt0911.github.io/</link><description>Recent content in CS 自学笔记 on CS Note</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>zh-CN</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 11:21:15 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://lzt0911.github.io/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>note</title><link>https://lzt0911.github.io/cs61b/note/</link><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 11:21:15 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://lzt0911.github.io/cs61b/note/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="lecture-1-intro-hello-world-java">Lecture 1 Intro, Hello World Java&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="hello-world">Hello World&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">HelloWorld&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">main&lt;/span>(String&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> args) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;hello world&amp;#34;&lt;/span>);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>All code in Java must be part of a class.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>We delimit(界定) the beginning and end of segments of code with &lt;code>{ }&lt;/code>.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>All statements in Java must end in a semi-colon(分号).&lt;/li>
&lt;li>For code to run we need &lt;code>public static void main(String[] args)&lt;/code>.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="variables-and-loops">Variables and Loops&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">HelloNumbers&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">main&lt;/span>(String&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> args) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span> x; &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Declare x exists and is an integer&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> x &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> 0;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">while&lt;/span> (x &lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;&lt;/span> 10) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(x);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> x &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> x &lt;span style="color:#f92672">+&lt;/span> 1;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="static-typing">Static Typing&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Before Java variables can be used, they must be declared.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Java variables must have a specific type.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Java variable types can never change.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>In Java, types are verified before the code runs! If there are type issues, the code will not compile.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>python code can crash due to type errors when its running.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>In Java, we can say &lt;code>System.out.println(5 + &amp;quot; &amp;quot;);&lt;/code>. But in Python, we can&amp;rsquo;t say &lt;code>print(5 + &amp;quot;horse&amp;quot;)&lt;/code>.
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Consider these two Java statements: &lt;code>String h = 5 + &amp;quot;horse&amp;quot;;&lt;/code> and &lt;code>int h = 5 + &amp;quot;horse&amp;quot;;&lt;/code>.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The first one will succeed, the second will give a compiler error. Since Java is strongly typed, if you tell it &lt;code>h&lt;/code> is a string, it can concatenate(连接) the elements and give you a string. But when &lt;code>h&lt;/code> is an &lt;code>int&lt;/code>, it can&amp;rsquo;t concatenate a number and a string and give you a number.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Python doesn&amp;rsquo;t constrain the type, and it can&amp;rsquo;t make an assumption for what type you want. Is &lt;code>x = 5 + &amp;quot;horse&amp;quot;&lt;/code> supposed to be a number? A string? Python doesn&amp;rsquo;t know. So it errors.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>In this case, &lt;code>System.out.println(5 + &amp;quot;horse&amp;quot;);&lt;/code>, Java interprets the arguments as a string concatentation, and prints out &amp;ldquo;5horse&amp;rdquo; as your result. Or, more usefully, &lt;code>System.out.println(5 + &amp;quot; &amp;quot;);&lt;/code> will print a space after your &amp;ldquo;5&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="defining-functions-in-java">Defining Functions in Java&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">LargerDemo&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">larger&lt;/span>(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span> x, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span> y) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">if&lt;/span> (x &lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;gt;&lt;/span> y) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">return&lt;/span> x;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">return&lt;/span> y;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">main&lt;/span>(String&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> args) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(larger(5, &lt;span style="color:#f92672">-&lt;/span>10));
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>To declare a function in Java, use &lt;code>public static&lt;/code> (仅限当前阶段).&lt;/li>
&lt;li>All parameters of a function must have a type, and the function itself must have a return type.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>All functions must be part of a class. In programming language terminology(术语), a function that is part of a class is called a &amp;ldquo;method&amp;rdquo;, so all functions in Java are methods.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>We refer to the entire string &lt;code>public static int larger(int x, int y)&lt;/code> as the method&amp;rsquo;s signature, as it lists the parameters, return type, name, and any modifiers(修饰符). Here our modifiers are &lt;code>public&lt;/code> and &lt;code>static&lt;/code>.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="arrays">Arrays&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> numbers &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>3&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>numbers&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>0&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> 4;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>numbers&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>1&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> 7;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>numbers&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>2&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> 10;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> numbers &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span>{4, 7, 10};
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(numbers.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">length&lt;/span>);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h1 id="lecture-2-defining-and-using-classes">Lecture 2 Defining and Using Classes&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="running-a-java-program">Running a Java Program&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>The most common way to execute a Java program is to run it through a sequence of two programs. The first is the Java compiler, or &lt;code>javac&lt;/code>. The second is the Java interpreter, or &lt;code>java&lt;/code>.
&lt;img src="https://lzt0911.github.io/images/CS61B/image-1.png" alt="alt text">
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ javac HelloWorld.java
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>$ java HelloWorld
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="static-methods">Static Methods&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Can&amp;#39;t be run directly, since there is no main method&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Dog&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>() {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Bark!&amp;#34;&lt;/span>);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Calls a method from another class&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">DogLauncher&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">main&lt;/span>(String&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> args) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> Dog.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>();
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="instance-variables-and-object-instantiation">Instance Variables and Object Instantiation&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Classes can contain not just functions, but also data.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Classes can be instantiated as objects.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The &lt;code>Dog&lt;/code> class has its own variables, also known as instance variables or non-static variables. These must be declared inside the class, unlike language Python or Matlab, where new variables can be added at runtime.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Dog&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span> weightInPounds; &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Instance variable&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Non-static method (Instance method)&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// If the method is going to be invoked by an instance of the class, then it should be non-static&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>() {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">if&lt;/span> (weightInPounds &lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;&lt;/span> 10) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;yip!&amp;#34;&lt;/span>);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">else&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">if&lt;/span> (weightInPounds &lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;&lt;/span> 30) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;bark!&amp;#34;&lt;/span>);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">else&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> System.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">out&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">println&lt;/span>(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;woof!&amp;#34;&lt;/span>);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">DogLauncher&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">main&lt;/span>(String&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> args) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> Dog d;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> d &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> Dog();
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> d.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">weightInPounds&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> 20;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> d.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>();
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="constructors-in-java">Constructors in Java&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Dog&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span> weightInPounds; &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Instance variable&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Constructor&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Determines how to instantiate the class&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Dog&lt;/span>(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">int&lt;/span> startingWeight) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> weightInPounds &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> startingWeight;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">DogLauncher&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">main&lt;/span>(String&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> args) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> Dog smallDog &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> Dog(5);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> smallDog.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>();
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> Dog hugeDog &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> Dog(150);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> hugeDog.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>();
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="array-instantiation-arrays-of-objects">Array Instantiation, Arrays of Objects&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">DogLauncher&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">void&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">main&lt;/span>(String&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> args) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> Dog&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[]&lt;/span> dogs &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> Dog&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>2&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>; &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Creates an array of Dog of size 2&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> dogs&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>0&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> Dog(8);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> dogs&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>1&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">new&lt;/span> Dog(20);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> dogs&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>0&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>();
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> dogs&lt;span style="color:#f92672">[&lt;/span>1&lt;span style="color:#f92672">]&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">makeNoise&lt;/span>();
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="static-vs-instance-methods">Static vs. Instance Methods&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Key differences between static and non-static methods:
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Static methods are invoked using the class name, e.g. &lt;code>Dog.makeNoise()&lt;/code>.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Instance methods are invoked using an instance name, e.g. &lt;code>smallDog.makeNoise()&lt;/code>.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Static methods can&amp;rsquo;t access &amp;ldquo;my&amp;rdquo; instance variables, because there is no &amp;ldquo;me&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Some classes are never instantiated. For example, &lt;code>Math&lt;/code>.
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>x &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> Math.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">round&lt;/span>(5.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">6&lt;/span>);
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>A class may have a mix of static and non-static members.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>It is useful for classes to have static variables. These are properties inherent(固有的) to the class itself, rather than the instance.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">class&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Dog&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> String binomen &lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Canis familiaris&amp;#34;&lt;/span>;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">static&lt;/span> Dog &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">maxDog&lt;/span>(Dog d1, Dog d2) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">if&lt;/span> (d1.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">weightInPounds&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;gt;&lt;/span> d2.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">weightInPounds&lt;/span>) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">return&lt;/span> d1;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">return&lt;/span> d2;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">public&lt;/span> Dog &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">maxDog&lt;/span>(Dog d2) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">if&lt;/span> (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">this&lt;/span>.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">weightInPounds&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;gt;&lt;/span> d2.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">weightInPounds&lt;/span>) {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">return&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">this&lt;/span>;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">return&lt;/span> d2;
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> }
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>}
